The paper deals with the edge dominating set problem, which is a fundamental problem in graph theory and has applications in various fields such as network design and social network analysis. The problem is related to graph algorithms and computational complexity, which are core topics in computer science. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), and cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
